						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying near the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1438, Dhāta, Nija, Śrāvaṇa śu. 11</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1516 A.D. August 8, Friday °50.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of a piece of land to the piper <hi rend="italic">(nāgasarāla)</hi> Chanōja for service in the temple of Chennakēśava of Niṭṭūru by <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Gōparāju, son of Tammayadēvachōḍa Mahārāju.</p>						

						</summary>
